('9ffac9d9-85c8-4d89-b1f0-04edb870150a','In fast changing markets, customers worldwide rely on Thales. Thales is a business where brilliant people from all over the world come together to share ideas and inspire each other. In aerospace, transportation, defence, security and space, our architects design innovative solutions that make our tomorrow''s possible.
<p>Assignment: Graduation/Afstudeeropdracht</p>
<p>Level: Higher vocational education, University (HBO/WO)</p>
<p>Field of study: Computer Science</p>
<p>Title of the assignment: Application Streaming in a Naval Cloud Environment</p>
<p><b><u>About us</u></b></p>
<p>In Nederland, waar 2000 medewerkers werkzaam zijn, hebben we vestigingen in vier steden: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven en Hengelo (hoofdkantoor). Samen met een uitgebreid ecosysteem van kennispartners, klanten en leveranciers werken we aan radars voor zeeschepen, cybersecurity-oplossingen, transportsystemen, communicatieapparatuur voor landstrijdkrachten, cryogene koeloplossingen en onderzoek &amp; ontwikkeling voor radartechniek (in samenwerking met TU Delft).</p>
<p>In the Netherlands, where 2000 employees are based, we are located in four cities: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven and Hengelo (HQ). Together with an extensive ecosystem of knowledge partners, customers and suppliers, we work on radars for naval vessels, cyber security solutions, transportation systems, communication equipment for land forces, cryogenic cooling solutions and research &amp; development for radar tech (in collaboration with TU Delft).<br></p>
<p><b><u>Information about the department</u></b></p>
<p>The software department of the Application Engineering cluster is responsible for the software development in Combat Management and Radar- and Optical sensors for worldwide navies- and defense systems. The work is performed in multi-disciplinary agile teams with specialists in software/system/test engineering and functional design.</p>
<p><b><u>About the assignment</u></b></p>
<p>In the world of IoT back-end processing power is becoming virtually unlimited and cloud platforms grow both in size and functionality. Streaming services and server-side rendering are becoming more and more facilitated. Interactive application steaming services like Google Stadia, Azure Remote Rendering and Amazon AppStream show possibilities of utilizing these functionalities.</p>
<p>Our TACTICOS Combat Management System provides a powerful back-end capable of enabling application streaming for naval use cases.</p>
<p>Your assignment will be to investigate how to use application streaming in the TACTICOS eco-system. This entails:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Researching the applicability</li>
 <li>Identifying relevant use cases</li>
 <li>Showing advantages and disadvantages of application streaming</li>
 <li>Demonstrating the concept</li>
</ul>
<p><u>Affinity</u></p>
<p>Linux, Cloud technology, OpenGL, Networking, Java, Web technology</p>
<p><b><u>Thales offers… </u></b></p>
